The paper deals with object detection and pose estimation, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The applications mentioned, such as robotics and augmented reality, suggest that the paper may also fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of unsupervised feature learning and next-best-view estimation indicates that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed framework on challenging datasets suggests that the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
